#: ../../api/core.md:1
msgid "Core: sessions and universes"
msgstr "Cœur : sessions et univers"

#: ../../api/core.md:3
msgid "`axiom.session`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.session:1 of
msgid "axiom/session.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.session:3 of
msgid "High-level public API of the Axiom engine (headless, zero Qt)."
msgstr "API publique de haut niveau du moteur Axiom (headless, zéro Qt)."

#: axiom.session:5 of
msgid ""
"A `Session` composes the engine building blocks (Arbitrator, "
"EventSourcer, CheckpointManager, VectorMemory) and exposes a synchronous "
"game loop that any application (GUI, CLI, server) can drive::"
msgstr ""
"Une `Session` compose les briques du moteur (Arbitrator, EventSourcer, "
"CheckpointManager, VectorMemory) et expose une boucle de jeu synchrone "
"que n'importe quelle application (GUI, CLI, serveur) peut piloter ::"

#: axiom.session:16 of
msgid ""
"Streaming happens through the `on_token` callback. The method is "
"synchronous: on the GUI side, the app wraps it in a QThread (see "
"workers/narrative_worker.py)."
msgstr ""
"Le streaming passe par le callback `on_token`. La méthode est synchrone :"
" côté GUI, l'app l'enveloppe dans un QThread (voir "
"workers/narrative_worker.py)."

#: axiom.session.IMAGE_GEN_STATUS:1 of
msgid ""
"Status string emitted right before contextual image generation starts. "
"Exposed as a constant so the GUI can react (e.g. show a placeholder) "
"without matching a hard-coded English message."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.session.Session:1 of
msgid "High-level wrapper to play one save of a universe."
msgstr "Enveloppe de haut niveau pour jouer une sauvegarde d'un univers."

#: ../../api/core.md axiom.session.Session.resolve_tick
#: axiom.session.Session.rewind axiom.session.Session.submit_intent
#: axiom.session.Session.take_turn of
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr "Paramètres"

#: axiom.session.Session:3 axiom.universe.Universe:5 of
msgid "Path of the universe file (.axiom / SQLite .db)."
msgstr "Chemin du fichier univers (.axiom / .db SQLite)."

#: axiom.session.Session:4 of
msgid "Identifier of the active save."
msgstr "Identifiant de la sauvegarde active."

#: axiom.session.Session:5 of
msgid "Pre-built LLM backend (see build_llm_from_config)."
msgstr "Backend LLM déjà construit (voir build_llm_from_config)."

#: axiom.session.Session:6 of
msgid ""
"Vector memory. If None, a `VectorMemory` is created under "
"`<data_dir>/vector/<save_id>` (or the app's default vector folder when "
"data_dir is None)."
msgstr ""
"Mémoire vectorielle. Si None, une `VectorMemory` est créée sous "
"`<data_dir>/vector/<save_id>` (ou le dossier vector par défaut de l'app "
"quand data_dir est None)."

#: axiom.session.Session:9 of
msgid ""
"Optional data root for path injection (only used for the default "
"VectorMemory)."
msgstr ""
"Racine de données optionnelle pour l'injection de chemins (utilisée "
"seulement pour la VectorMemory par défaut)."

#: axiom.session.Session:11 of
msgid "Game mode ('Normal', 'Hardcore', 'Companion')."
msgstr "Mode de jeu ('Normal', 'Hardcore', 'Companion')."

#: axiom.session.Session:12 of
msgid ""
"Optional backend for the hero's decision (Companion mode). If None, "
"lazily built from the config (local `extraction_model`), like the worker "
"does."
msgstr ""
"Backend optionnel pour la décision du héros (mode Compagnon). Si None, "
"construit paresseusement depuis la config (modèle local "
"`extraction_model`), comme le fait le worker."

#: axiom.session.Session.turn_id:1 of
msgid "Number of the last played turn (0 if the game has not started)."
msgstr "Numéro du dernier tour joué (0 si la partie n'a pas commencé)."

#: axiom.session.Session.submit_intent:1 of
msgid "Submit an action intent to the pool for the current turn."
msgstr "Soumet une intention d'action au pool pour le tour courant."

#: ../../api/core.md axiom.session.Session.list_checkpoints
#: axiom.session.Session.resolve_tick axiom.session.Session.rewind
#: axiom.session.Session.submit_intent axiom.session.Session.take_turn
#: axiom.universe.Universe.list_saves of
msgid "Return type"
msgstr "Type de retour"

#: axiom.session.Session.resolve_tick:1 of
msgid "Resolve every intent currently in the pool as a single tick."
msgstr "Résout toutes les intentions actuellement dans le pool en un seul tick."

#: axiom.session.Session.take_turn:1 of
msgid "Run a full turn (synchronously) and return the result."
msgstr "Exécute un tour complet (de façon synchrone) et retourne le résultat."

#: axiom.session.Session.take_turn:3 of
msgid "Wraps `submit_intent` and `resolve_tick` for backward compatibility."
msgstr "Enveloppe `submit_intent` et `resolve_tick` pour la rétrocompatibilité."

#: axiom.session.Session.rewind:1 of
msgid "Bring the save back to its state at turn `target_turn_id`."
msgstr "Ramène la sauvegarde à son état au tour `target_turn_id`."

#: axiom.session.Session.rewind:3 of
msgid ""
"Invalidates the Arbitrator's stats cache and resynchronises `turn_id`. "
"Returns the summary provided by `CheckpointManager.rewind`."
msgstr ""
"Invalide le cache de stats de l'Arbitrator et resynchronise `turn_id`. "
"Retourne le résumé fourni par `CheckpointManager.rewind`."

#: axiom.session.Session.list_checkpoints:1 of
msgid "List the turns for which a checkpoint (snapshot) exists."
msgstr "Liste les tours pour lesquels un checkpoint (snapshot) existe."

#: axiom.session.Session.regenerate_variant:1 of
msgid "Regenerate a variant of turn `turn_id`'s narrative text."
msgstr "Régénère une variante du texte narratif du tour `turn_id`."

#: axiom.session.Session.regenerate_variant:3 of
msgid ""
"Replays the same player message to produce an alternative text (without "
"re-evaluating rules or stats); the variant is appended to the turn's "
"multiverse payload and becomes active. Delegates to `axiom.regenerate`."
msgstr ""
"Rejoue le même message joueur pour produire un texte alternatif (sans "
"réévaluer règles ni stats) ; la variante est ajoutée au payload multivers"
" du tour et devient active. Délègue à `axiom.regenerate`."

#: axiom.session.Session.regenerate_variant:8 of
msgid ""
"event-sourced history (`user_input`/`narrative_text`) up to the previous "
"turn."
msgstr ""
"historique event-sourcé (`user_input`/`narrative_text`) jusqu'au tour "
"précédent."

#: axiom.session.Session.current_stats:1 of
msgid "Current materialised stats per entity (rebuilds the State_Cache)."
msgstr "Stats matérialisées courantes par entité (reconstruit le State_Cache)."

#: axiom.session.Session.current_stats:3 of
msgid ""
"Public API: rebuilds the cache from the Event_Log first, so external "
"callers always get a guaranteed-consistent snapshot. In-engine hot paths "
"use `_read_state_cache()` instead (the cache is already kept fresh)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../api/core.md
msgid "Returns"
msgstr "Renvoie"

#: axiom.session.Session.current_stats:7 of
msgid "Mapping of entity_id to a dict of stat_key to stat_value strings."
msgstr "Correspondance entity_id → dict de stat_key vers stat_value (chaînes)."

#: ../../api/core.md:10
msgid "`axiom.universe`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.universe:1 of
msgid "axiom/universe.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.universe:3 of
msgid ""
"Headless representation of an Axiom universe (a `.axiom` file = SQLite "
"database)."
msgstr ""
"Représentation headless d'un univers Axiom (un fichier `.axiom` = base "
"SQLite)."

#: axiom.universe:5 of
msgid ""
"Exposes the metadata (name, system prompt) and the list of saves, with no"
" Qt dependency whatsoever. Entry point: `Universe.load(path)`."
msgstr ""
"Expose les métadonnées (nom, prompt système) et la liste des sauvegardes,"
" sans la moindre dépendance Qt. Point d'entrée : `Universe.load(path)`."

#: axiom.universe.Universe:1 of
msgid "A loaded universe (read-only view of its metadata)."
msgstr "Un univers chargé (vue en lecture seule de ses métadonnées)."

#: axiom.universe.Universe:9 of
msgid "Display name of the universe."
msgstr "Nom affiché de l'univers."

#: axiom.universe.Universe:13 of
msgid "Founding system prompt handed to the narrator."
msgstr "Prompt système fondateur transmis au narrateur."

#: axiom.universe.Universe.load:1 of
msgid "Load a universe from its SQLite file."
msgstr "Charge un univers depuis son fichier SQLite."

#: axiom.universe.Universe.load:3 of
msgid "Path to the existing universe file."
msgstr "Chemin vers le fichier univers existant."

#: axiom.universe.Universe.load:5 of
msgid "A `Universe` instance populated from `Universe_Meta`."
msgstr "Une instance `Universe` peuplée depuis `Universe_Meta`."

#: axiom.universe.Universe.list_saves:1 of
msgid "List this universe's saves (separate save files + embedded legacy ones)."
msgstr ""
"Liste les sauvegardes de cet univers (fichiers séparés + legacy "
"embarquées)."

